<item>
            <title>[SOLR-832] Rows parameter is not honored during import in some cases</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-832</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The rows parameter is not honored in non-debug mode.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;During debug mode, the rows parameter for a new request resets the old value. Therefore, the import will abort immediately, if rows is not specified on a subsequent request and if the original value for rows was greater than the default (10).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The first one is an enhancement and the second is a major bug. The fix for both is very related and it is best to handle both in the same issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
